(23, 'historical avant-garde and the failure of liberalism', '<p>in the following passage, Yudice considers the rise of the avant-garde in response to the conceived failure of the liberalism in competition in the global market in the 20th century.</p>', 1, 274, '2021-05-19 14:26:03', '2021-05-19 14:26:03'),
(24, 'bears some resemblance to iran', '<p>on a ground, the resemblance can be seen in the different approach to culture between Farah and Mehradad Pahlbod. The former was closer to the bourgeois avant-garde position which sought to offer a synthesis of vernacular culture; the latter however, displayed an oligarchic tendencies and sides with Europeanizing. </p>', 1, 280, '2021-05-20 01:17:23', '2021-05-20 01:17:23'),
